I.	Copy selected text to clipboard (copy/paste buffer)
1.		Command + C
II.	Paste from buffer
1.		Command +V
III.	Cut selected text to buffer (selected text is deleted)
1.		Command + X
IV.	Save current file in VSCode
1.		Command + S
V.	Toggle block comment in VSCode
1.		Shift + Option + A 
VI.	Toggle line comment in VSCode
1.		Command + / 
VII.	Move cursor from word to word right
1.		Option + Right Arrow 
VIII.	Move cursor from word to word left
1.		Option + Left Arrow 
IX.	Select word right
1.		Shift + Option + Right Arrow 
X.	Select word left
1.		Shift + Option + left arrow
XI.	Select all contents
1.		Command + A 
XII.	Select current line, including end of line character
1.		Command + Shift + Right Arrow or Left Arrow 
XIII.	Jump to start of line
1.		Command + Left Arrow
XIV.	Jump to end of line
1.		Command + Right Arrow 
XV.	Jump to beginning of current file
1.		Command + Home + up

